#---------------------------------------------------------------------- 
# SOCKET

Q: What is the difference between INET and UNIX socket?
AF_INET uses the TCP/IP protocol. AF_UNIX creates filesystem objects and it only works between processes on the same host. AF_UNIX is much faster than AF_INET.

Q: What is DBUS?
DBUS is a framework around UNIX socket used initially by KDE (and now other free desktop environments)
DBUs is middleware
Both one-to-one messaging and publish/subscribe communication are supported.
D-Bus is aware of user identities and does support flexible authentication mechanisms and access controls. The system bus may see traffic from and to any number of user identities.
More @ http://www.freedesktop.org/wiki/IntroductionToDBus

